Your going to kick yourself.

The signature of map is:

    &lt;R&gt; Stream&lt;R&gt; map(Function&lt;? super T,? extends R&gt; mapper)

The important part is that the argument is of type `Function&lt;? super T,? extends R&gt; mapper` where `? super T` is the element of the mapped stream (in your case `Bucket`) and `? extends R` is the **return type** (in your case `BucketDTO`).

In order for the compiler to work out the return type the anonymous function has to actually return a typed Object. In your case this is the fix:

    buckets.stream()
        .map(
             bucket -&gt; {
            	 return new BucketDTO(); // NB: so the compiler can work out the return class of the anonymous method
             }
        )
        .collect(Collectors.toList());

